postcontent: I have a rare early Taurus PT-92 for sale or trade. This is an 82-83 vintage weapon, it has the heel European style safety of the Beretta 92 original model. Most PT-92 magazines have both style cuts so not a big deal on magazines, I just want one a little newer. These are known to be much higher in quality than the newest PT-92s, they always find ways to make em a little cheaper. This weapon appears unfired and includes original magazine, box, warrranty card and a big fold out info poster with a parts breakdown. title: For Sale/Trade:  Gently used Daniel Defense M4 5.56 NATO
postcontent: I am a Federal Firearms Dealer (or FFL) that means you will have to do ATF form 4473 paperwork. This is also listed on Gunbroker. For sale is a gently used Daniel Defense M4 rifle. This has a 16” barrel and a 15” picatinny 1913 rail. This rifle has 7 quick detach flush cups for QD sling swivels. It has a Advanced Armament 51T flash hider / suppressor adaptor to drastically reduce the muzzle flash, and can be used as a glass breaker, striking tool and adaptor for a Advanced Armament suppressor. This has just over 500 rounds through this rifle, (550 to be exact.) This comes with •Rifle, •two 30 round magazines made by Okay Industries with green followers, •two large buttstock pads, •Daniel Defense sticker and •Daniel Defense hard case. I’m only selling this because I have switched over to 10.5” barrel Daniel Defense Mk18s so I never use this rifle. This rifle’s original owner was in law enforcement and kept this in great condition. This was his personal rifle. No gimmicks, I just don’t need this rifle anymore.
